      <lg xml:id="MTA70">
<l>collun taṉaiyun toḻumiṉ viḻumuṭampu</l>
<l>cellun taṉaiyun tirumālai – nallitaḻt</l>
<l>tāmattāl vēḷviyāṟ ṟantirattāṉ mantirattā</l>
<l>ṉāmattā lēttutirē ṉaṉṟu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>As long as there is speech, worship [him]. As long as the body that will fall</l>
<l>[still] goes on, it is good if you praise<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">ēttutirēl has to be analysed as one of the transitional conditional forms where the suffix -ēl is added not only to an absolutive but even to a finite verb (here a subjunctive 2.pl.). </note> Tirumāl with strands</l>
<l>of good petals, with sacrifice, with ritual acts,</l>
<l>with mantras [and] with names.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
